# ============================================================
# Trivy ignore list for the DB image (postgres:16-alpine)
#
# Section A — gosu stdlib CVEs
# All entries affect the Go standard library (stdlib) inside the
# gosu v1.19 binary shipped by postgres:16-alpine (Go 1.24.6).
#
# Root cause:  gosu has not yet released a build with Go >=1.25.10
#              (which contains the upstream fixes).  The postgres
#              Docker image team ships whatever gosu version exists
#              at image build time.
#
# Checked:     postgres:16-alpine AND postgres:17-alpine both carry
#              gosu 1.19 / go1.24.6 — no fixed upstream image is
#              available as of 2026-06-04.
#
# Risk:        gosu is a privilege-dropping helper called once at
#              container startup (it exec's postgres as the postgres
#              user and then exits).  It never opens network sockets,
#              processes HTTP, or validates TLS certificates at
#              runtime, so the attack surface for all crypto/tls,
#              net/url, and net/http CVEs below is effectively zero.
#
# Action:      Remove section A when postgres:16-alpine ships with
#              gosu >= 1.20 compiled against Go >= 1.25.10 / 1.26.3.
#
# Section B — libxml2 alpine CVE
# CVE-2026-6732 affects libxml2 2.13.9-r0 in alpine 3.23.x.
# Fix: 2.13.9-r1 (available in alpine edge as of 2026-06-04).
# apk upgrade in the Dockerfile will install the fix once alpine
# 3.23 ships the patched package.
# Risk: libxml2 is a parse-only library used by postgres internals;
# the affected XSD validation path is not reachable externally.
# Action: Remove CVE-2026-6732 when postgres:16-alpine base ships
#         with libxml2 >= 2.13.9-r1.
# ============================================================

# Section A — gosu / Go stdlib (no fixed gosu release available)
CVE-2025-68121
CVE-2025-61726
CVE-2025-61729
CVE-2026-25679
CVE-2026-32280
CVE-2026-32281
CVE-2026-32283
